  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine patient variables, physician presenter variables,
      and information variables that might affect clinical decision making in asymptomatic carotid
      stenosis. The hypothesis is that information variables are the most significant determinant
      of clinical decision making.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
